This paper is primarily focused on Compositional Game Theory (CGT), which is a subfield of Game Theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT. The paper also deals with the computer science idea of compositionality, which falls under the category of cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper introduces a new operator on games, which can be seen as an application of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with the equilibria of games, which can be seen as a topic in Distributed Systems (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the concept of subgame perfection, which is a topic in Mechanism Design (cs.MA).
